        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 7:23PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 723 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Cut Bank, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cut Bank.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
